s it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":1,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":14,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":23,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Trelawney was born in 1314, in Cornwall, England, his father, John de Trelawney, was 19 and his mother, Lady Laura Lucy Sergeaux, was 17. He married Margery De Reparijs in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1340, in Launceston, Cornwall, England, at the age of 26."},"et":{"1314–1340":"1314–1340","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1335–1370":"1335–1370","1295–1334":"1295–1334","1297–1336":"1297–1336","before 1314":"enne 1314","1297":"1297","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1370":"1370","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1314":"1314","1336":"1336","1335":"1335","1334":"1334","about 1336":"umbes 1336","1453":"1453","1328":"1328","1317":"1317",",, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St Mabyn, Cornwall, England":"St Mabyn, Cornwall, England","Launceston, Co